<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000">
<A HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<P>Al Cowlings continued to assert his Fifth Amendment privilege against self-incrimination on April 26, 1996, the third day of his deposition. "Why don't you just give me immunity, and I can answer these questions for you," Cowling told the plaintiffs' lawyers. Two months later, Judge Alan Haber denied granting Cowlings limited immunity against prosecution. Cowlings finished his deposition on May 15. Judge Haber's ruling means that Cowlings does not have to answer further questions in a deposition.</P>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
