Q: You are looking at your calendar, for the record -- 
 
A: Right. 
 
Q: -- Exhibit 168.  Continue. 
 
A: Right.  Talked to my cousin later that afternoon. 
 
Q: Who is your cousin? 
 
A: Christa Oetjen, O-e-t-j-e-n. 
 
Q: And what is her phone number? 
 
A: [Deleted telephone number] 
 
Q: She works in Los Angeles and lives here? 
 
A: Right. 
 
Q: Did you discuss with her anything about O.J. Simpson? 
 
A: I certainly did. yeah. 
 
Q: What did you say? 
 
A: I talked to her about Nicole's death and I talked to her about Faye 
being in rehab, you know, just trying to relate some of my thoughts 
to her. 
 
Q: Now, by this time did you know that O.J. was a suspect? 
 
A: It's really difficult for me to discern what point I became aware 
that the police considered him a suspect. 
 
Q: When is that point? 
 
A: I think it probably was in the day before the funeral. 
 
Q: What was it?  Just a media report? 
 
A: Yeah. 
 
Q: Now, when you heard that -- Well, let me back up again.  Finish 
off what you did in relation to Mr. Simpson on the 15th. 
 
A: Actually, I was going to a concert that evening, but I didn't go. 
 
Q: Did you talk to any of Nicole's friends?  Cora Fischman, Cici 
Shahian? 
 
A: Probably Kris Jenner -- Kris Jenner and Bruce Jenner were 
probably the only two people that I talked to about this case in that 
time. 
 
Q: Okay. 
 
A: Might have briefly talked to Paul about Francesca, called over to 
Paul's house about Francesca, but that's it. 
 
Q: Was anybody developing any information to support this idea of 
