entire period of time -- 
 
A: That's correct. 
 
Q: -- as opposed to some other place; right? 
 
A: No.  Actually the 4th and 5th I went to San Diego. 
 
Q: June 4th and June 5th you were out of town those two nights? 
 
A: Right. 
 
Q: So you do not know whether Faye spent those in her condo or 
not; right? 
 
A: That's correct. 
 
Q: You never took her keys away; right? 
 
A: No. 
 
Q: So it is fair to say that you don't know how many nights she 
spent at Nicole's house during the first 12 days of June; true? 
 
A: That's correct. 
 
Q: You do not even know if she spent any nights there, do you? 
 
A: That's right.  Well, no, that is not correct. I know that she called 
me in San Diego, repeatedly throughout the night from Nicole's 
house. 
 
Q: What night was that? 
 
A: That would be Saturday the 4th.   
 
Q: And what was the -- 
 
