pursuing an investigation -- 
     
A: Yes. 
     
Q: -- for the real killers?  Have you discussed this again with him 
since that time? 
     
A: No. No. 
     
Q: You've never discussed this investigation again? 
     
A: No. 
     
Q: Okay. Has he ever indicated to you the status of any 
investigation? 
     
A: No. 
     
Q: Has he ever indicated to you they have any leads as to who the 
real killers might be? 
     
A: No. 
     
Q: Has he ever indicated to you he has turned up some evidence 
that indicates he wasn't guilty of these murders? 
     
A: No. 
     
Q: Have you ever just asked him point-blank whether he was 
innocent of these murders? 
     
A: I never asked him. 
     
Q: After this one conversation you had about investigators and the 
real killers, when was the next time you spoke to him? 
 
A: I guess it was during the time where he was going to have the 
kids.  It was I think around October.  It was Sydney's birthday.  I 
don't know.  Around that time.  And he wanted to know if [Name 
Deleted] would like to go with them.  You know, he said that 
Sydney would like to have [Name Deleted] with her. 
     
Q: Okay. [Name Deleted] did go with her, didn't she? 
     
A: Yes. 
     
Q: And they went to --  
     
A: Yes. 
     
Q: -- Neverland? Okay.  How many days was that for? 
     
A: Just all day. 
     
Q: Okay.  Did -- Simpson went with them.  Right? 
     
A: Yes. 
     
Q: Okay.  Did you go with them for that? 
     
A: No. 
     
Q: And did you have any discussions with Simpson at that time 
about the murder, real killers or investigation or anything? 
     
A: No. 
     
Q: Okay.  And when was the next time after that? 
     
A: Next time was when the kids -- when he had the kids again, and 
so he called me where to bring [Name Deleted] at the time, 
because at the time the kids were not at Rockingham. 
     
Q: Okay. And did you bring them somewhere else? 
     
A: Yeah. 
     
Q: Was that [Name Deleted]'s house, do you remember? 
  
A: Yes, Don [Name Deleted]'s house, yes. 
     
Q: Okay.  And did you visit with him for any period of time when 
you took the kids down there? 
     
A: No.  I just dropped [Name Deleted], and then [Name Deleted] 
spent the night there with Sydney, and then I went to -- because at 
the time I wanted to see Sydney.  That's the first time I've seen 
Sydney since, you know, this whole thing, because I said I wanted 
to see the kids, so that was it.  And then the following day I went 
to pick up [Name Deleted]. 
     
Q: Okay. No real conversations --  
 
A: No. 
     
Q: -- at that time? 
     
A: No. 
 
Q: Okay.  Has there been any time since then where you've been 
over at Rockingham and sat down and visited with Mr. Simpson 
for any length of time? 
     
A: That's pretty much what happened. 
     
Q: Okay.  Well, you said you had had some meals over there, too. 
     
A: Meals is when the kids were there right, yes. 
     
Q: Okay.  But sit-down ones with Simpson there, too? 
     
A: Well, one time was the Christmas -- we were exchanging gifts.  
That was Christmas Day.  He invited us, the whole family, to his 
house. 
     
Q: Did you have any discussions with him then or -- 
     
A: About what? 
     
Q: About the murders. 
     
A: No. 
 
Q: About Nicole? 
     
A: Well, we always, you know -- sometimes things like, "This is 
what Nicole would love. This is" -- you know, that's pretty much 
what we -- 
     
Q: Any discussion of any investigation? 
 
A: No. 
     
Q: And the only attorney you have spoken to with Mr. Simpson is 
