Q: Do you remember an incident at Los Brisas or Las Brisas 
where you were with Faye Resnick, Nicole, Cici and Ron 
Fischman and O.J. Simpson and Christian Reichardt in which the 
Simpsons started going on a tirade against smoking?  Do you 
remember that? 
     
MR. BAKER: Argumentative. Vague.  Leading. 
     
THE WITNESS: What's "tirade" mean?  It's like angry and stuff? 
     
BY MR. PETROCELLI: 
 
Q: Yes, angry --  
     
A: No, it was not-it was a conversation.  I wouldn't say an angry 
conversation, no. 
     
Q: But he was protesting the smoking by the women.  Right? 
     
A: Yeah. 
     
Q: Okay.  And he got so loud that the women got up and walked 
out of the restaurant.  True? 
     
MR. BAKER: Leading -- 
      
THE WITNESS: No -- 
     
MR. BAKER: -- argumentative. 
 
THE WITNESS: -- that's not true. 
     
BY MR. PETROCELLI: 
     
Q: Did you get up to leave because he was speaking so loudly? 
     
Q: No.  We got up because -- no.  They got up first.  Faye and 
Nicole got up first and -- to have -- to smoke, and that was it, and 
then I followed them. 
     
Q: So while Simpson is ranting and raving about smoking, Nicole 
and Faye get up to go out and have a cigarette. 
     
MR. BAKER: Argumentative -- 
     
BY MR. PETROCELLI: 
       
Q: Is that right? 
     
MR. BAKER: Argumentative -- 
       
THE WITNESS: No -- 
     
MR. KRAMER: Let him finish his objection. 
 
MR. BAKER: Argumentative.  Vague.  Leading. 
     
You can answer. 
     
THE WITNESS: It wasn't that way, no.  It wasn't that ranting and 
raving.  We were just -- we were talking, you know.  There was no 
argument then. 
     
BY MR. PETROCELLI: 
 
Q: Not at all. 
       
A: No. 
     
Q: It was a friendly, pleasant, affable discussion.  Is that --  
     
A: No -- 
 
Q: -- what you're saying? 
     
A: -- I wouldn't say friendly.  It was like we were debating the 
pros and con of smoking. 
     
Q: What was Simpson's point of view in that debate? 
     
A: That he doesn't like -- he's a non-smoker. 
     
Q: He didn't like Nicole smoking.  True? 
     
A: He didn't like Nicole smoking, yeah. 
     
Q: He would never buy her a cigarette lighter, would he? 
     
MR. BAKER: Speculation. Argumentative. 
     
THE WITNESS: (No audible response.) 
 
BY MR. PETROCELLI: 
     
Q: Did you ever see him --  
     
MR. KELLY: Was there an answer -- I'm sorry.  Was there an 
answer to that? 
     
MR. PETROCELLI: I'm waiting for the answer. 
     
THE WITNESS: Oh, I didn't know I thought you were just -- 
    
BY MR. PETROCELLI: 
     
Q: He wouldn't buy her -- based on what you observed and knew 
of Mr. Simpson's position about Nicole's smoking, you don't think 
he would buy her a cigarette lighter, do you? 
     
MR. BAKER: Same objections. 
     
THE WITNESS: Yes, I guess so. 
     
BY MR. PETROCELLI: 
     
Q: You guess what? 
     
A: Why would someone buy someone -- I don't know.  I mean, 
why would -- if you're a non-smoker --  
     
Q: Exactly.  That wouldn't make sense to you.  Correct? 
     
A: Correct. 
     
Q: You ever see a gold Cartier cigarette lighter that Nicole got in 
the last months of her life? 
     
A: I never saw that.  I didn't see it. 
 
MR. PETROCELLI: Okay. 
     
EXAMINATION BY MR. BAKER: 
     
Q: On June 14th what time did you arrive at the Bundy condo? 
     
MR. KRAMER: This is the Tuesday? 
 
MR. BAKER: The Tuesday. 
     
Q: June 14th, what time did you arrive at the Bundy condo? 
     
A: Later afternoon. 
       
Q: Who was there? 
     
A: Who was there? 
       
Q: (Nods head.) 
     
A: The Browns -- I mean, you know the girls, Tanya, Denise and 
Dominique, and then A.C. and Ron Hardy.. 
     
Q: And how long had they been there?  Do you know? 
     
A: When I was there, they were all there already, so I don't know 
how long. 
     
Q: Did anyone tell you what time they arrived on June 14th? 
     
A: I don't know what time, no.  Nobody told me. 
     
Q: How did you get into the condominium on June 14? 
     
A: The gate was open because Ron Hardy was cleaning the front 
yard. 
     
Q: The gate was open on Bundy? 
       
A: Yeah. 
 
Q: And Ron Hardy was kind of cleaning the walkway? 
     
A: Right. 
     
Q: How was he cleaning it? 
       
A: Hosing it. 
 
Q: Did you talk to him while he was hosing the walkway? 
       
A: No, not really, no. 
     
Q: He was just using one of the hoses --  
       
A: Yeah, right. 
     
